<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3786632>
    dc:description "Fig. 1. A- medially narrow sternite, typical for males in Sisyphus. B- Abdominal sternite in females of Sisyphus species; C- Sisyphus; bears strong setae on the external edge of the first metatarsus; D- Neosisyphus, lacking strong setae on the external margin of the first metatarsus. E- Complete lateral ridge, which divides proepisternum from pronotal disc in Sisyphus. F- Lateral ridge does not reach antero-lateral edge of the pronotum in Neosisyphus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3786632/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3786679>
    dc:description "Fig. 23. Image of the habitus of the tibialis species-group: A. N. mirabilis." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3786679/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3786681>
    dc:description "Fig. 24. Image of the aedeagus of the tibialis species-group: A. N. mirabilis." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3786681/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3786666>
    dc:description "Fig. 17. Images of the habitus of the barbarossa species-group: A. N. barabrossa; B. N. calcaratus; C. N. tembyi sp. n, arrow showing a diagnostic feature for the new species; D. N. setiger." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3786666/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

