<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3786634>
    dc:description "Fig. 2. Images of the habitus of the muricatus species-group: A. S. muricatus; B. S. neobornemisszanus; C. S. fasciculatus; D. S. perissinottoi; E. S. manni; F. S. swazi sp. n. G. S. alveatus. I. Fully developed hind wing, which is typical to most of Sisyphus species in southern Africa H. Brachypterous hind wing of S. alveatus. J. Sclerite represents a reduced hind wing of S. swazi sp. n." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3786634/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3786636>
    dc:description "Fig. 3. Images of the aedeagi of the muricatus species-group: A. S. muricatus; B. S. neobornemisszanus; C. S. fasciculatus; D. S. perissinottoi; E. S. manni; F. S. swazi sp. n; G. S. alveatus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3786636/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3786640>
    dc:description "Fig. 5. Images of the habitus of the goryi species-group: A. S. bicuariensis sp. n; with enphasis of the black and gray setae on pronotum and elytra; B. S. caffer; C. S. genierorum; D. S. goryi; E. S. sordidus.F. Pronotal setae originate from the posterior edge or between ocellate points. G. Pronotal setae arise from the centre of ocellate punctures, commonly seen in S. genierorum, S. sordidus; S. perissinottoi; S. manni and S. swazi sp. n. H. Tufts of setae on the epipleurae visible from above." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3786640/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3786646>
    dc:description "Fig. 8. Images of the habitus of the umbraphilus species-group: A. S. umbraphilus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3786646/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3786642>
    dc:description "Fig. 6. Images of the aedagi of the goryi species-group: A. S. bicuariensis sp. n; B. S. caffer; C. S. genierorum; D. S. goryi; E. S. sordidus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3786642/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3786652>
    dc:description "Fig. 11. Images of the habitus of the costatus species-group: A. S. impressipennis; B. S. costatus; C. S. gazanus; D. S. inconspicuus sp. n; E. S. australis sp. n. F. elytra composed of alternate rows of well and less-developed setae, normally seen in S. costatus and S. australis sp. n. G. Head of S. costatus shows a concavity between the medial teeth on the anterior edge of the clypeus. H. Head of S. australis sp. n shows a straight margin between the medial teeth on the anterior edge of the clypeus; there are defined carinae on the clypeo-frontal suture, and scattered punctation on the vertex. I. Frons of S. inconspicuus sp. n without clear punctation. J. S. gazanus: bearing vertex and frons densely and fully punctate." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3786652/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3786654>
    dc:description "Fig. 12. Images of the aedeagi of the costatus species-group: A. S. impressipennis; B. S. costatus; C. S. gazanus; D. S. inconspicuus sp. n; E. S. australis sp. n." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3786654/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3786660>
    dc:description "Fig. 14. Images of the habitus of the seminulum species-group: A. S. splendidus; B. S. oralensis; C. S. nanniscus; D. S. auricomus sp. n. Pronotal setation and punctation patterns of S. oralensis (E), and S. auricomus sp. n (F)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3786660/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3786662>
    dc:description "Fig. 15. Images of the aedeagi of the seminulum species-group: A. S. oralensis; B. S. nanniscus; C. S. auricomus sp. n." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3786662/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

